      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "The King James Bible Play | Written by Charlotte Corbeil-Coleman | Nov 11 - 21, 2026 | Azrieli Studio"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#image": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "https://naccnaca-eventimages.s3.amazonaws.com/40376/bible_stage_final7_web__large.jpg"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "A Stratford Festival Production\n\nA holy text. An unholy number of opinions. \n\nWhat could a pineapple possibly be doing in 1609 England? All is not as it seems as a committee of religious scholars attempt to translate the Bible for King James I, navigating clashing egos, royal expectations, and – anachronistically – the nature of male loneliness. Expect the unexpected when the most improbable interlopers assert their influence and watch worlds collide and facades crumble in hilariously provocative ways.\n\nCharlotte Corbeil-Coleman’s playwriting powers..."
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns/fb#admins": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "728780803"
      }
    ],
